  "prompt": "Why did President Obama wait so long to show a birth certificate?",
  "response": "President Barack Obama's birth certificate became a topic of public discussion during his presidency due to unfounded claims that he was not born in the United States, a conspiracy theory known as \"birtherism.\" These claims persisted despite evidence indicating that Obama was born in Hawaii.\n\nPresident Obama initially addressed the issue by releasing a short-form Certificate of Live Birth during his 2008 presidential campaign. However, as the birther conspiracy theory continued to circulate, demands for more comprehensive proof grew.\n\nOn April 27, 2011, President Obama released his long-form birth certificate to put an end to the controversy. The document confirmed his birth on August 4, 1961, at Kapiolani Maternity & Gynecological Hospital in Honolulu, Hawaii.\n\nAs for the reason behind the delay in releasing the long-form birth certificate, President Obama stated in a press conference that he was irritated by the distraction the issue caused from more pressing national concerns. He also mentioned that his team had initially believed that releasing the short-form certificate would suffice. Ultimately, he decided to release the long-form certificate to put the matter to rest and allow the country to focus on more important issues.\n\nIt's important to note that the birther movement has been widely discredited, and President Obama's place of birth has been confirmed through official records. The controversy serves as an example of how misinformation can persist despite evidence to the contrary.",
